00:20:54.130 --> 00:20:56.860 align:middle line:84%
The Dashka Stone is a
controversial artifact

00:20:56.860 --> 00:21:00.160 align:middle line:84%
that is believed by some
to be the guidelines used

00:21:00.160 --> 00:21:04.880 align:middle line:84%
by the architect of the world
known as the Map of the Creator.

00:21:04.880 --> 00:21:07.390 align:middle line:84%
The stone tablet has
baffled researchers

00:21:07.390 --> 00:21:10.510 align:middle line:90%
since its discovery in 1999.

00:21:10.510 --> 00:21:13.510 align:middle line:84%
As impossible as it may
seem, Russian experts

00:21:13.510 --> 00:21:18.880 align:middle line:84%
believe the stone map could
be 120 million years old.

00:21:18.880 --> 00:21:22.480 align:middle line:84%
The Dashka slab depicts not
only the environs of the Ural

00:21:22.480 --> 00:21:26.330 align:middle line:84%
Mountains but also a series
of civil engineering projects,

00:21:26.330 --> 00:21:32.020 align:middle line:84%
including 7,457 miles of
channels, several dams,

00:21:32.020 --> 00:21:35.450 align:middle line:84%
and hieroglyphic notations
of unknown origin.

00:21:35.450 --> 00:21:37.870 align:middle line:84%
The accuracy and
perspective of the map

00:21:37.870 --> 00:21:40.480 align:middle line:84%
suggests that it was
created from an aerial point

00:21:40.480 --> 00:21:41.780 align:middle line:90%
of observation.

00:21:41.780 --> 00:21:44.930 align:middle line:84%
The hieroglyphs have not,
as of this time of writing,

00:21:44.930 --> 00:21:47.440 align:middle line:84%
been deciphered but are
thought to be related

00:21:47.440 --> 00:21:50.470 align:middle line:90%
to an ancient form of Chinese.

00:21:50.470 --> 00:21:54.200 align:middle line:84%
Archeologists from the Bashkir
State University discovered

00:21:54.200 --> 00:21:57.860 align:middle line:84%
the Dashka Stone in the Ural
Mountains of Eastern Russia

00:21:57.860 --> 00:22:00.780 align:middle line:90%
on July the 21st, 1999.

00:22:00.780 --> 00:22:02.870 align:middle line:84%
The discoverers were
immediately struck

00:22:02.870 --> 00:22:04.680 align:middle line:90%
by the size of the tablet.

00:22:04.680 --> 00:22:09.980 align:middle line:84%
It measures 58 inches high, 42
inches wide, and 6 inches thick

00:22:09.980 --> 00:22:12.030 align:middle line:90%
and weighs 1 ton.

00:22:12.030 --> 00:22:14.660 align:middle line:84%
Upon further examination,
the researchers

00:22:14.660 --> 00:22:16.080 align:middle line:90%
were even more stunned.

00:22:16.080 --> 00:22:18.710 align:middle line:84%
The tablet appears to
show a highly accurate

00:22:18.710 --> 00:22:22.910 align:middle line:84%
topographical map of Bashkiria,
a specific area of the Ural

00:22:22.910 --> 00:22:25.680 align:middle line:84%
Mountains at a scale
of approximately 1

00:22:25.680 --> 00:22:28.250 align:middle line:90%
to 1.1 kilometers.

00:22:28.250 --> 00:22:32.270 align:middle line:84%
Alexandr Chuvyrov, a professor
at Bashkir State University, who

00:22:32.270 --> 00:22:34.670 align:middle line:84%
led the team, named
the stone Dashka

00:22:34.670 --> 00:22:38.460 align:middle line:84%
in honor of his grandfather,
who was born on that day.

00:22:38.460 --> 00:22:41.870 align:middle line:84%
He said, "At first sight, I
understood that this was not

00:22:41.870 --> 00:22:45.750 align:middle line:84%
a simple stone piece, but a
real map, and not a single map,

00:22:45.750 --> 00:22:47.580 align:middle line:90%
but a three-dimensional.

00:22:47.580 --> 00:22:49.580 align:middle line:90%
You can see it yourself."

00:22:49.580 --> 00:22:53.220 align:middle line:84%
The Map of the Creator is
comprised of three levels,

00:22:53.220 --> 00:22:56.450 align:middle line:84%
strongly suggesting that it
didn't originate in nature

00:22:56.450 --> 00:22:58.560 align:middle line:90%
but was artificially made.

00:22:58.560 --> 00:23:01.040 align:middle line:84%
The first layer is
roughly 7 inches

00:23:01.040 --> 00:23:04.890 align:middle line:84%
of a cement or ceramic
compound based on dolomite.

00:23:04.890 --> 00:23:07.400 align:middle line:84%
The second layer
is roughly 1 inch

00:23:07.400 --> 00:23:11.130 align:middle line:84%
of diopside glass
enriched with silicon.

00:23:11.130 --> 00:23:13.910 align:middle line:84%
The third layer is only
a few millimeters thick

00:23:13.910 --> 00:23:16.950 align:middle line:84%
and is made of
calcium-porcelain mixture,

00:23:16.950 --> 00:23:19.560 align:middle line:84%
perhaps to give the
tablet added protection,

00:23:19.560 --> 00:23:23.420 align:middle line:84%
or perhaps to create a diffused
light to better illuminate

00:23:23.420 --> 00:23:24.300 align:middle line:90%
the stone.

00:23:24.300 --> 00:23:26.700 align:middle line:84%
"How did we manage to
identify the place?"

00:23:26.700 --> 00:23:27.750 align:middle line:90%
Said Chuvyrov.

00:23:27.750 --> 00:23:31.560 align:middle line:10%
"At first, we couldn't imagine
the map was so ancient.

00:23:31.560 --> 00:23:34.310 align:middle line:10%
Happily, relief of
today's Bashkiria

00:23:34.310 --> 00:23:37.330 align:middle line:10%
has not changed so much
within millions of years.

00:23:37.330 --> 00:23:41.030 align:middle line:84%
We could identify Ufa
Height, while Ufa Canyon is

00:23:41.030 --> 00:23:44.000 align:middle line:84%
the main point of our proofs
because we carried out

00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:48.020 align:middle line:84%
geological studies and found its
track where it must be according

00:23:48.020 --> 00:23:49.430 align:middle line:90%
to the ancient map.

00:23:49.430 --> 00:23:51.500 align:middle line:84%
Displacement of
the canyon happened

00:23:51.500 --> 00:23:54.690 align:middle line:84%
because of tectonic slabs
which moved from east.

00:23:54.690 --> 00:23:57.050 align:middle line:84%
The group of Russian
and Chinese specialists

00:23:57.050 --> 00:24:01.530 align:middle line:84%
in the field of cartography,
physics, mathematics, geology,

00:24:01.530 --> 00:24:03.920 align:middle line:84%
chemistry, and Old
Chinese language

00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:07.220 align:middle line:84%
managed to precisely find
out that the slab contains

00:24:07.220 --> 00:24:10.170 align:middle line:84%
the map of the Ural
region, with the rivers.

00:24:10.170 --> 00:24:13.700 align:middle line:90%
Belaya, Ufimka, Sutolka.

00:24:13.700 --> 00:24:16.160 align:middle line:84%
You can also see Ufa
Canyon, the break

00:24:16.160 --> 00:24:19.100 align:middle line:84%
of the earth's crust stretched
out from the city of Ufa

00:24:19.100 --> 00:24:21.920 align:middle line:90%
to the city of Sterlitamak.

00:24:21.920 --> 00:24:26.030 align:middle line:84%
At the moment, Ursak River
runs over the former canyon."

00:24:26.030 --> 00:24:28.190 align:middle line:84%
The Dashka Stone
undoubtedly points

00:24:28.190 --> 00:24:31.190 align:middle line:84%
to a Ural civilization more
advanced than previously

00:24:31.190 --> 00:24:32.250 align:middle line:90%
suspected.

00:24:32.250 --> 00:24:36.260 align:middle line:84%
However, the claims that it
was made 120 million years ago

00:24:36.260 --> 00:24:39.960 align:middle line:84%
by a geographic creator
are most likely false.

00:24:39.960 --> 00:24:42.530 align:middle line:84%
The Bashkir researchers
derived this date

00:24:42.530 --> 00:24:47.010 align:middle line:84%
from a pair of ancient seashells
found locked in the stone slab.

00:24:47.010 --> 00:24:51.360 align:middle line:84%
The first shell could be as
old as 500 million years old.

00:24:51.360 --> 00:24:55.470 align:middle line:84%
The second shell could be
as old as 120 million years.

00:24:55.470 --> 00:24:58.370 align:middle line:84%
Why these shells, still
intact, were incorporated

00:24:58.370 --> 00:25:02.580 align:middle line:84%
into the tablet or if they
were purposely included at all,

00:25:02.580 --> 00:25:04.500 align:middle line:84%
they cannot be
known for certain.

00:25:04.500 --> 00:25:08.160 align:middle line:84%
Scientists suspect that,
aside from the ancient shells,

00:25:08.160 --> 00:25:11.400 align:middle line:84%
the tablet was made
approximately 3,000 years ago.

00:25:11.400 --> 00:25:13.610 align:middle line:84%
However, it's
exceedingly difficult

00:25:13.610 --> 00:25:17.390 align:middle line:84%
to radiocarbon date the
engravings themselves.

00:25:17.390 --> 00:25:20.060 align:middle line:84%
Great attention has
been paid to the variety

00:25:20.060 --> 00:25:23.930 align:middle line:84%
of magnificent megalithic
structures around the world,

00:25:23.930 --> 00:25:27.530 align:middle line:84%
yet very little is reported on
the mysterious and impressive

00:25:27.530 --> 00:25:30.440 align:middle line:84%
set of stone structures that
can be found in the Ural

00:25:30.440 --> 00:25:31.760 align:middle line:90%
Mountains of Russia.

00:25:31.760 --> 00:25:35.460 align:middle line:84%
In the Sverdlovsk Oblast
region in the middle Urals,

00:25:35.460 --> 00:25:37.880 align:middle line:84%
there can be found
numerous dolmens.

00:25:37.880 --> 00:25:40.080 align:middle line:84%
According to controversial
descriptions,

00:25:40.080 --> 00:25:42.890 align:middle line:84%
a dolmen is a type of
single-chambered megalithic

00:25:42.890 --> 00:25:43.690 align:middle line:90%
tomb.

00:25:43.690 --> 00:25:45.800 align:middle line:84%
However, there is
really no evidence

00:25:45.800 --> 00:25:49.350 align:middle line:84%
to suggest that they were
initially constructed as tombs.

00:25:49.350 --> 00:25:52.460 align:middle line:84%
Rather, it seemed that
subsequent civilizations chose

00:25:52.460 --> 00:25:54.590 align:middle line:90%
to use them for this purpose.

00:25:54.590 --> 00:25:58.370 align:middle line:84%
Dolmens are usually comprised
of two or more vertical stones

00:25:58.370 --> 00:26:01.470 align:middle line:84%
supporting a flat
horizontal stone on top.

00:26:01.470 --> 00:26:05.270 align:middle line:84%
There can be variations ranging
from relatively simple to very

00:26:05.270 --> 00:26:06.240 align:middle line:90%
complex.

00:26:06.240 --> 00:26:08.720 align:middle line:84%
The dolmens in the
Urals are considered

00:26:08.720 --> 00:26:11.070 align:middle line:84%
to be small compared
to other dolmens,

00:26:11.070 --> 00:26:15.560 align:middle line:84%
ranging from approximately
1.5 to 2.5 meters in width

00:26:15.560 --> 00:26:16.460 align:middle line:90%
and length.

00:26:16.460 --> 00:26:20.060 align:middle line:84%
There is some variance in the
dolmens of the Urals with two

00:26:20.060 --> 00:26:21.510 align:middle line:90%
distinct styles.

00:26:21.510 --> 00:26:23.690 align:middle line:84%
The stone plate
dolmens are created

00:26:23.690 --> 00:26:27.210 align:middle line:84%
with a mound of stones that
have an attached chamber.

00:26:27.210 --> 00:26:30.020 align:middle line:84%
These usually have a
square court in front

00:26:30.020 --> 00:26:33.000 align:middle line:84%
and are sometimes surrounded
by smaller stones.

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:35.990 align:middle line:84%
The boulder dolmens are
constructed from large boulders

00:26:35.990 --> 00:26:37.620 align:middle line:90%
that form a chamber.

00:26:37.620 --> 00:26:41.000 align:middle line:84%
The chamber is covered by
one or more flat stones.

00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:43.100 align:middle line:84%
There is some
variation in structure

00:26:43.100 --> 00:26:44.490 align:middle line:90%
of the boulder dolmens.

00:26:44.490 --> 00:26:46.850 align:middle line:84%
But they all have
two entrance points--

00:26:46.850 --> 00:26:49.790 align:middle line:84%
a main entrance to the
side and a small entrance

00:26:49.790 --> 00:26:52.010 align:middle line:90%
between boulders.

00:26:52.010 --> 00:26:54.680 align:middle line:84%
The menhirs are the
most typical type

00:26:54.680 --> 00:26:56.790 align:middle line:90%
of megalith found in the Urals.

00:26:56.790 --> 00:26:59.490 align:middle line:84%
A menhir is a single
vertical stone.

00:26:59.490 --> 00:27:03.300 align:middle line:84%
They can be found singularly
as a monolith or in groups.

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:07.010 align:middle line:84%
The menhirs found in the Urals
include monoliths and groupings

00:27:07.010 --> 00:27:09.360 align:middle line:90%
and tend to be roughly finished.

00:27:09.360 --> 00:27:11.750 align:middle line:84%
All of the monoliths
discovered to this point

00:27:11.750 --> 00:27:14.720 align:middle line:84%
are located near either a
settlement or a cemetery

00:27:14.720 --> 00:27:19.100 align:middle line:84%
from the Bronze
Age, 3300 to 600 BC.

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:23.730 align:middle line:84%
Some of the many groups are
in rows, 13 to 18 meters long.

00:27:23.730 --> 00:27:26.960 align:middle line:84%
A circular shaped structure
was discovered at the village

00:27:26.960 --> 00:27:29.930 align:middle line:90%
of Akhunovo in Bashkiria.

00:27:29.930 --> 00:27:32.690 align:middle line:84%
Eight menhirs are formed
into a circular shape

00:27:32.690 --> 00:27:36.190 align:middle line:84%
that is approximately
25 meters in diameter.

00:27:36.190 --> 00:27:38.930 align:middle line:84%
While the dolmens and
menhirs are amazing

00:27:38.930 --> 00:27:42.290 align:middle line:84%
and mysterious structures
themselves, the most amazing

00:27:42.290 --> 00:27:46.400 align:middle line:84%
find in the Urals are the
megaliths of Vera Island in Lake

00:27:46.400 --> 00:27:47.810 align:middle line:90%
Turgoyak.

00:27:47.810 --> 00:27:50.370 align:middle line:90%
Dating to the Eneolithic period.

00:27:50.370 --> 00:27:53.980 align:middle line:84%
These megaliths are referred
to as Megalith Number 1,

00:27:53.980 --> 00:27:58.140 align:middle line:84%
Megalith Number 2, Megalith
Number 3, Vera Island 9,

00:27:58.140 --> 00:27:59.950 align:middle line:90%
and Vera Island 4.

00:27:59.950 --> 00:28:03.300 align:middle line:84%
Megalith Number 1 is the
largest megalith structure

00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:06.760 align:middle line:84%
on the island, standing
at 16 by 9 meters.

00:28:06.760 --> 00:28:10.090 align:middle line:84%
Its cut into the bedrock
and covered with capstones.

00:28:10.090 --> 00:28:14.080 align:middle line:84%
It's orientated towards the west
and includes a long entrance,

00:28:14.080 --> 00:28:17.470 align:middle line:84%
a central hall, and two chambers
with a connecting corridor.

00:28:17.470 --> 00:28:21.100 align:middle line:84%
It includes windows and
sculptures of bulls and wolves.

00:28:21.100 --> 00:28:25.320 align:middle line:84%
It's speculated that megalith
number one served as a temple

00:28:25.320 --> 00:28:26.910 align:middle line:90%
at some point.

00:28:26.910 --> 00:28:30.250 align:middle line:84%
Megalith Number 2, pictured
in the feature image,

00:28:30.250 --> 00:28:33.690 align:middle line:84%
was found carved into a rocky
slope with a mound structure

00:28:33.690 --> 00:28:34.630 align:middle line:90%
covering it.

00:28:34.630 --> 00:28:38.490 align:middle line:10%
It's orientated north and
contained two chambers connected

00:28:38.490 --> 00:28:39.930 align:middle line:10%
by a corridor.

00:28:39.930 --> 00:28:43.470 align:middle line:84%
Megalith Number 3 is
created by large boulders

00:28:43.470 --> 00:28:46.480 align:middle line:84%
with a square pit cut
into the center rock.

00:28:46.480 --> 00:28:48.840 align:middle line:84%
It's closed off by
vertical stone slabs

00:28:48.840 --> 00:28:51.550 align:middle line:84%
with massive boulders
as capstones.

00:28:51.550 --> 00:28:55.750 align:middle line:84%
Vera Island 9 is a cultic
ritual place with two menhirs,

00:28:55.750 --> 00:28:58.770 align:middle line:84%
while Vera Island 4 is a
cultic place surrounded

00:28:58.770 --> 00:29:02.880 align:middle line:84%
by vertical stones with a
small menhir in the center.

00:29:02.880 --> 00:29:06.850 align:middle line:84%
The megaliths of the Urals are
undoubtedly an impressive sight.

00:29:06.850 --> 00:29:09.060 align:middle line:84%
Yet strangely,
virtually nothing is

00:29:09.060 --> 00:29:11.950 align:middle line:84%
known about who created
them, how they were built,

00:29:11.950 --> 00:29:14.910 align:middle line:84%
or what purpose they
were intended to serve.

00:29:14.910 --> 00:29:18.400 align:middle line:84%
The megaliths stretch across
an immense area of land,

00:29:18.400 --> 00:29:22.140 align:middle line:84%
suggesting that they were not
all created by a single group.

00:29:22.140 --> 00:29:24.840 align:middle line:84%
Megalith Number 1
on Vera Island is

00:29:24.840 --> 00:29:27.010 align:middle line:84%
believed to have been
a temple at some point.

00:29:27.010 --> 00:29:30.150 align:middle line:84%
However, other megaliths
present no obvious signs

00:29:30.150 --> 00:29:33.310 align:middle line:84%
that they were used for
any religious purposes.

00:29:33.310 --> 00:29:35.820 align:middle line:84%
Nevertheless, it's
possible that the megaliths

00:29:35.820 --> 00:29:40.170 align:middle line:84%
had a common use in spite of
the variances in size and shape.

00:29:40.170 --> 00:29:43.140 align:middle line:84%
It's hoped that further
archeological research may

00:29:43.140 --> 00:29:47.350 align:middle line:84%
help to unravel the mysteries
of these spectacular structures,

00:29:47.350 --> 00:29:52.730 align:middle line:84%
as well as the civilization that
created them many millennia ago.